{"id":"mai-n5q3","kind":"ticket","type":"task","title":"CRDT docs layer — ywasm + wazero for character-level merge","tags":["architecture","crdt","docs","epic"],"body":"Build the docs materialization layer on y-crdt (Yjs Rust implementation) via ywasm + wazero.\n\nArchitecture:\n  maitake (Go) → wazero (WASM runtime) → ywasm → yrs (Rust)\n\nOne prebuilt ywasm .wasm file vendored in the repo. Pure Go build, no cgo, no Rust toolchain needed by users.\n\nPhase 1: ywasm integration\n- Build ywasm.wasm from y-crdt repo\n- Go wrapper around wazero to call YDoc/YText operations\n- Serialize/deserialize YDoc state for storage in git notes\n\nPhase 2: Doc notes (kind: doc)\n- Store YDoc state as base64 in note body (or separate blob)\n- mai docs sync materializes YDoc → markdown files on disk\n- File edits detected by diffing, converted to YText insert/delete ops\n- Changes flow back into the YDoc in the note\n\nPhase 3: Bidirectional sync\n- Obsidian edits → diff → YText ops → note update → git push\n- Agent note edits → YText ops → materialize → file update\n- Concurrent edits merge via YATA algorithm (character-level CRDT)\n- No conflicts, no skips, deterministic merge\n\nConfig: docs dir configurable in .maitake/config (default: docs/)\nFrontmatter: materialized files get mai-id in YAML frontmatter for round-tripping.\n\nReferences:\n- y-crdt: github.com/y-crdt/y-crdt (Rust, Apache 2.0)\n- ywasm: WASM target of yrs\n- wazero: github.com/tetratelabs/wazero (Go WASM runtime, Apache 2.0)\n- YATA paper: researchgate.net/publication/310212186","timestamp":"2026-03-28T20:25:43Z","branch":"main"}
